external_knowledge:
- 'Nike knights' refers to players sponsored by Nike; 
- 'Million-dollar tournaments' means events with a total prize money greater than $1,000,000; 
- 'Round table of at least ten players' refers to events with at least 10 participating players.

- 'crown jewel' of sponsorships refers to 'Title Sponsor' (the primary or most prestigious sponsor);
- 'outshone the average' means having an average score greater than the specified threshold (average total points > 100);
- 'century mark' refers to a score of 100.
